'As soon as I knew we'd been broken into, I went upstairs and checked him right away and I kissed him so hard,' the boy's relieved father Thinh Lee told KTRK.

The suspect, who has still not been caught, climbed into the family's home through a first-story window that had been left unlocked.

Le said he believes the teenager knew he was being filmed because he sometimes looked towards the cameras but continued anyway.

He is recorded walking from room to room in the house for about five minutes before entering the toddler's bedroom. His parents did not wake during the break-in.

